  "text": "clinics were at high-risk of having OSA, and the majority were not diagnosed. [CITATION_1] Coronary artery disease (CAD) is the leading cause of mortality in adults, and it remains responsible for about one-third or more of all deaths in individuals over age 35 years. [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] Epidemiological studies have shown a strong association between OSA and hypertension and metabolic syndrome as major risk factors for CAD.",
